{"lemma":"رِيفِ","slug":"رِيفِ","root":"ر.#.ف","root_slug":"ر-_-ف","root_link":"/words/roots/ر-_-ف","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":2},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n14297","n17283"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B1%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%81%D9%90"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"countryside, rural area, thorp land"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to give rural character too"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"An ancient borrowing of Egyptian r(ꜣ)-pr (“temple”), due to agricultural properties (i.e., lands) in Egypt—which Bedouins roamed—having been administered by temples. The similarity to Akkadian 𒊑𒅁𒄣 (ri-ip-qu /⁠ripqu⁠/, “field broken up for cultivation”) is coincidental.\n\nEtymology tree\nEgyptian r(ꜣ)\nEgyptian pr\nEgyptian r(ꜣ)-prbor.\nArabic رِيف (rīf)denom.\nArabic ريف\nDenominal verb from رِيف (rīf)."},"ipa":["/riːf/","/raj.ja.fa/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n14297","headword_ar":"رَيِفٌ","root":"rA^f","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see the next preceding paragraph."}],"source_refs":[]},{"entry_id":"n17283","headword_ar":"رِيفٌ","root":"ryf","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Land in which are sown fields,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seedproduce, and abundance of herbage and of the goods"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"conveniences"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comforts of life:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) and (K) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that is near to water, of the land of the Arabs,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, O, L, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of other lands:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, L:) or the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"part that is near to the Sawád"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Als~awaAd","text_ar":"السَّوَاد"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of the land of the Arabs:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IDrd, Ham p. 676:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tract in which are green herbs, and waters,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, O, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and level lands of seed-produce,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sown fields,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"varieties of seed-produce:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) [generally,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a region, district,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tract,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of cultivated fields;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of towns,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"villages, and of cultivated land:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 676:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroyaAfN","text_ar":"اَرْيَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, M, TA) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ruyuwfN","text_ar":"رُيُوفٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (M, TA.) ―         -b2-  Also (M, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Abundance"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of herbage, and of the goods, conveniences,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"comforts, of life, and"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in respect of food"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Lth, T, M, O, K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"drink:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K:) pl. [in this sense]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroyaAfN","text_ar":"اَرْيَافٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K) only. (M.) See also 4."}],"source_refs":["S","O","K","M","L","T","TA","Lth"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}